Detect negative pion and deuteron in
coincidence.
The particle identification for forward
particles

x4codes.hlp: Nat.lab.for High Energy Physics, Oho, Ibaraki, Japan

x4freetext: pi-2 beam line
Used to detect the recoil deuterons. The
momentum resolution of the forward arm of the
spectrometer which consisted of an analyzer
magnet, five sets of MWPC`s, and three sets of
SC`s was +-2.5 %.
Five sets of MWPC`s (forward arm) are used to
detect the recoil deuteron and two sets of
MWPC`s (backward arm) are used to detect the
scattered pions.
Three sets of SC`s (forward arm) are used to
detect the recoil deuteron and two sets of SC`s
(backward arm) are used to detect the scattered
pions.
Used to reject electron contamination in the
incident beam
An overall normalization uncertainty was
estimated to be 8%
Maximum of systematic value is +-10%. Typical
value is +-7%. (Not mentioned in the
reference, but given in private
communication.)
Statistical error
1. Glauber approximation ([Ref. K. Kanai et
al., Prog. Theor. Phys. 62, 153(1979), and 65,
2. Phase shift analysis ([Ref. N. Hiroshige et
al., Prog. Theor. Phys. 68, 327(1982).])
Data (fig. 1, p1839 in reference) taken from
the Durham HEP Data bases (AKEMOTO 83) with
author`s confirmation
